'''哥倫比亞中心'''（{{lang-en|'''Columbia Center'''}}，原稱：'''Bank of America Tower'''和'''Columbia Seafirst Center'''）是[[美國|美國]][[西雅圖|西雅圖]]市中心的一座[[摩天大樓|摩天大樓]]，以約{{convert|284.2|m}}的高度成為西雅圖最高建築，位於第四和第五大道相交處。按實際可居住層數算，是[[華盛頓州|華盛頓州]]最高建築，此外也是美國西海岸僅次於[[聯邦銀行大廈|聯邦銀行大廈]]的第二高建築。地上76層，地下7層，因此成為密西西比河以西層數最多的建築。<ref name="emporis"/> 大廈第73層上有一個[[觀景台|觀景台]]。

==設計==

哥倫比亞中心的設計人是建築師切斯特·L·林德賽（Chester L. Lindsey），<ref name="Lindsey obit">{{cite news |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/news/article/Chester-Lindsey-dead-at-76-Architect-changed-1122076.php |title=Chester Lindsey dead at 76: Architect changed look of Seattle's skyline |author=Susan Phinney |date=August 18, 2003 |newspaper=Seattle Post-Intelligencer |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2019-05-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517030201/https://www.seattlepi.com/news/article/Chester-Lindsey-dead-at-76-Architect-changed-1122076.php |dead-url=no }}</ref> 地基使用花崗岩。大廈側體有三個幾何形凹面，因為頂部次第錯開兩次，因此看起來像是三座緊挨着的高度不一的建築。<ref name="Howard S. Wright" />

此建築最初設計的高度是{{convert|306.5|m}}。但因為靠近[[西雅圖-塔科馬國際機場|西雅圖-塔科馬國際機場]]，[[美國聯邦航空總署|美國聯邦航空總署]]不允許其達到此高度，此外當時城市法規限制最高建築不得超過50層。但因為還有法律說明若大廈基層用作零售，則可以另外增加高度，因此開發商馬丁·塞利格（Martin Selig）依然將其建成了76層。<ref>{{cite news |title=Building towers over Seattle |date=May 3, 1984 |newspaper=Anchorage Daily News |agency=UPI |author=Terry Finn |url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=8B8fAAAAIBAJ&sjid=facEAAAAIBAJ&pg=1536,1141837&dq=columbia-center+land-use+loophole&hl=en}}</ref><ref name="Egan 1986" />

實際上該建築最初就被提議叫做哥倫比亞中心，但剪綵時使用的名稱是Columbia Seafirst Center，以紀念其最大的資助商Seafirst Bank。1983年，該銀行被[[美國銀行|美國銀行]]收購，因此改名美國銀行塔（Bank of America Tower），當時還有昵稱為“BOAT”即（'''B'''ank '''o'''f '''A'''merica '''T'''ower的縮寫）。2005年11月，美國銀行開始從該建築中撤出，因此名稱改回最早的哥倫比亞中心。不過美國銀行至今在該建築中仍有辦公室和一個分行。<ref name="naming">{{cite news |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2002638565_columbiatower22.html |title=Region's loftiest building renamed |date=November 22, 2005 |author=Tom Boyer |newspaper=Seattle Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2005-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051130082143/http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2002638565_columbiatower22.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==歷史==

馬丁·塞利格（Martin Selig）是當地著名的地產開發商，1981年貸款2.05億美元以建造該建築。<ref name="Egan 1986">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1986/06/29/realestate/focus-seattle-creating-an-office-empire.html?pagewanted=all |title=Creating An Office Empire |date=June 29, 1986 |author=Timothy Egan |work=The New York Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2019-05-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519062339/https://www.nytimes.com/1986/06/29/realestate/focus-seattle-creating-an-office-empire.html?pagewanted=all |dead-url=no }}</ref> 建築公司是霍華德·H·懷特（Howard S. Wright），建築在1985年1月12日建成，<ref name="Howard S. Wright">{{cite web |url=http://www.howardswright.com/projects/detail/bank-of-america-tower-formerly-columbia-seafirst-tower/ |title=Bank of America Tower (formerly Columbia Seafirst Tower) |publisher=Howard S. Wright |accessdate=June 13, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160116181007/http://www.howardswright.com/projects/detail/bank-of-america-tower-formerly-columbia-seafirst-tower/ |archivedate=2016年1月16日 }}</ref> 同年3月2日付諸使用。<ref name="Lindsey obit" /> [[美國鋼鐵公司|美國鋼鐵公司]]為其提供了{{convert|16,000|ST|MT}}的鋼鐵。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1983/02/26/business/us-steel-move-draws-fire.html |title=U.S. Steel Move Draws Fire |date=February 26, 1983 |agency=AP |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2019-05-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518061743/https://www.nytimes.com/1983/02/26/business/us-steel-move-draws-fire.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 比原先的西雅圖最高建築[[西雅圖第一國民銀行大廈|西雅圖第一國民銀行大廈]]（1969年建成，{{convert|630|ft|m}}）高出將近一半。1989年因財政問題，開發商正式以3.54億美元的價格將此建築賣給Seafirst Bank。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://articles.latimes.com/1989-11-20/business/fi-194_1_martin-selig |title=Selig Undaunted After Selling His Seattle Skyscraper |date=November 20, 1989 |newspaper=Los Angeles Times |author=Bill Dietrich |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2017-06-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170613201326/http://articles.latimes.com/1989-11-20/business/fi-194_1_martin-selig |dead-url=no }}</ref>

1989年的市民替代方案（Citizen's Alternative Plan）對西雅圖市中心建築高度作出了嚴格的限制，<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/1989/11/26/realestate/national-notebook-seattle-project-tailored-to-space-limits.html |title=Project Tailored To Space Limits |date=November 26, 1989 |author=Harriet King |newspaper=The New York Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2019-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516214338/https://www.nytimes.com/1989/11/26/realestate/national-notebook-seattle-project-tailored-to-space-limits.html |dead-url=no }}</ref> 因此1990年預定的{{convert|300|ft|m}}的天線建造計劃被駁回，<ref>{{cite news |title=Height plan reduced on Seattle towers |date=August 7, 1984 |agency=UPI |url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=oUAeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=mMAEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6962,3986417&dq=columbia-seafirst-center&hl=en}}</ref> 而計劃由兩個{{convert|192|ft|m}}的天線取而代之。<ref name="antennas">{{cite news |url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19900105&slug=1049301 |title=Tallest Building To Reach Higher -- City Issues Permit For Seafirst Antennas |date=January 5, 1990 |author=Robert T. Nelson |newspaper=Seattle Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2018-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224052931/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=19900105&slug=1049301 |dead-url=no }}</ref> 但直到1994年許可到期，天線仍然沒能建成。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/stories/1999/08/02/daily18.html |title=Taller antennas sought for Columbia Center |date=August 6, 1999 |newspaper=Puget Sound Business Journal |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2014-02-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140203033139/http://www.bizjournals.com/seattle/stories/1999/08/02/daily18.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

Equity Office在1998年以4.04億美元的價格買下該建築。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/business/article/Interested-in-share-of-76-story-tower-1217207.php |title=Interested in share of 76-story tower? |author=Andrea James |date=October 13, 2006 |newspaper=Seattle Post-Intelligencer |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2019-05-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190516070356/https://www.seattlepi.com/business/article/Interested-in-share-of-76-story-tower-1217207.php |dead-url=no }}</ref> 紐約州公共退休基金持有49.9%的股份，但幾年後又賣回給了Equity Office。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20061013&slug=columbia13 |title=Pension fund puts stake in Columbia Center up for sale |author=Amy Martinez |date=October 13, 2006 |newspaper=Seattle Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2016-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161202101433/http://community.seattletimes.nwsource.com/archive/?date=20061013&slug=columbia13 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.costar.com/News/Article/EOP-Pares-Portfolio-Before-Sale-To-Blackstone/85748 |title=EOP Pares Portfolio Before Sale To Blackstone |date=January 9, 2007 |author=Jillian Ambroz |publisher=CoStar |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2018-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224113038/http://www.costar.com/News/Article/EOP-Pares-Portfolio-Before-Sale-To-Blackstone/85748 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> 2007年被賣給現擁有者Beacon Capital。<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.costar.com/News/Article/Blackstone-Completes-Seattle-Sale-to-Beacon/89530 |title=Blackstone Completes Seattle Sale to Beacon |date=May 2, 2007 |author=Kiran Umapathy |publisher=CoStar |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2018-02-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180224113134/http://www.costar.com/News/Article/Blackstone-Completes-Seattle-Sale-to-Beacon/89530 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2011431935_columbia25.html |title=Columbia Center misses mortgage payment |date=March 24, 2010 |author=Eric Pryne |newspaper=Seattle Times |accessdate=2013-12-28 |archive-date=2012-07-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120702230344/http://seattletimes.nwsource.com/html/businesstechnology/2011431935_columbia25.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://beaconcapital.com//currentportfolio.php |title=Current Portfolio |publisher=Beacon Capital Partners |accessdate=June 12, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022105951/http://beaconcapital.com/currentportfolio.php |archivedate=2012年10月22日 |df= }}</ref>

===911===

2004年6月16日，[[9/11委員會|9/11委員會]]報告聲稱[[九一一襲擊事件|九一一襲擊事件]]最初的目標還包括“加利福尼亞和華盛頓州最高建築”，即哥倫比亞中心和洛杉磯的聯邦銀行大廈。<ref>{{cite paper | author= | title=Outline of the 9-11 Plot, Staff Statement No. 16, | page=13 | format= | publisher=National Commission on Terrorist Attacks | url=http://www.9-11commission.gov/staff_statements/staff_statement_16.pdf | date=16 June 2004 | accessdate=10 June 2012 | archive-date=2020-03-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320032738/https://9-11commission.gov/staff_statements/staff_statement_16.pdf | dead-url=yes }}</ref>

